trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that can iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en opplisting som kan gå gjennom samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators only allow reading the data in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratorene tillater bare lesing av data i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratorene kan ikke brukes til å endre den underliggende samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first item in the collection.
trans-unit.target: I utgangspunktet er enumeratoren plassert før det første elementet i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>henter også enumeratoren tilbake til denne plasseringen.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: På dette Plasser, kaller <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>oppstår det et unntak.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first item of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Du må derfor kalle <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>å flytte enumeratoren til det første elementet i samlingen før leser <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>Returnerer det samme objektet før enten <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>eller <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next item.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>angir <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>til neste element.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: After the end of the collection is passed, the enumerator is positioned after the last item in the collection, and calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Etter at slutten av samlingen er utløpt, enumeratoren er plassert etter det siste elementet i samlingen, og kall <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerer `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: Hvis siste kall til <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerte `false`, kall <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>oppstår det et unntak.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first item of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Angi <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>til det første elementet i samlingen på nytt, kan du kalle <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>etterfulgt av <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: En opplisting forblir gyldig så lenge samlingen forblir uendret.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying or deleting items, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du endrer til i samlingen, for eksempel å legge til, endring eller sletting av elementer, enumeratoren ugyldiggjøres, og neste kall eller <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>oppstår en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> will return the item that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis samlingen er endret mellom <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>og <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>returnerer elementet som den er satt til, selv om enumeratoren ugyldiggjøres allerede.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratoren har ikke eksklusiv tilgang til samlingen. lister opp i en samling er derfor gjelder ikke en sikker-prosedyre.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads could still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Selv når en samling synkroniseres, kan andre tråder fortsatt endre samlingen, som fører til at enumeratoren til Iverksett et unntak.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen eller opp unntak som er et resultat av endringer foretatt av andre tråder.

trans-unit.source: Searches for the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrame"></xref> and returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence within the entire collection.
trans-unit.target: Søk etter den angitte <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrame"> </xref> og returnerer den nullbaserte indeksen for den første forekomsten i hele samlingen.

trans-unit.source: The collection is searched forward starting at the first key frame and ending at the last key frame.
trans-unit.target: Samlingen er søkt gjennom Videresend starter på den første key rammen og slutter på den siste key rammen.

trans-unit.source: This method performs a linear search; therefore, the average execution time is proportional to <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden utfører en lineær søket. Gjennomsnittlig kjøringstid er derfor proporsjonalt <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>

trans-unit.source: That is, this method is an O(*n*) operation, where *n* is <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Det vil si denne metoden er en O (*n*) operasjonen, der *n* er <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BooleanKeyFrameCollection.Count%2A>

trans-unit.source: Gets a value that indicates whether access to the collection is synchronized (thread-safe).

trans-unit.source: Enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Lister opp i en samling vil si gjelder ikke sikker.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads could still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Selv når en samling synkroniseres, kan andre tråder fortsatt endre samlingen, som fører til at enumeratoren til Iverksett et unntak.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen eller opp unntak som er et resultat av endringer foretatt av andre tråder.
